<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870917-0149 </DOCNO><HL> Credit Ratings:Williams Cos. IssuesAre Upgraded by Sandamp;P</HL><DD> 09/17/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WMBBOND MARKET NEWS (BON)STOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Standard andamp; Poor's Corp. upgraded about $1.4 billion of Williams Cos. long-term debt and preferred stock, removing the issues from its CreditWatch list.    Williams' debentures were raised to triple-B-minus from double-B-plus, its Northwest Pipeline Corp. unit's debentures and preferred stock to triple-B from triple-Bminus and its Williams Natural Gas Co.'s debentures and preferred stock to triple-B from triple-B-minus.    The ratings concern cited a drop in debt leverage, cash flow &quot;well in excess of current capital needs&quot; and conservative financial policies. Williams is an oil and gas pipeline transmission and fiber optic telecommunications concern based in Tulsa, Okla. </TEXT></DOC>